title: Lumia 950 and 950XL accidentally listed on Microsoft Store online
text:
Other Articles This is our India pricing. These are not special prices, or introductory prices: Janne Einola, H&M India Asus to partner Foxconn to make smartphones in Andhra Pradesh Renault to start Kwid delivery by mid-October Ahead of Windows 10 devices, Microsoft has listed its two new Lumia flagships on its store online. The listing shows both the devices to be unlocked models and comply with the specifications leaked earlier.
According to the listing, Microsoft Lumia 950 will feature a 5.2-inch WQHD display while the Lumia 950XL will come with a larger 5.7-inch WQHD display. Both the device will come with 20-megapixel camera with Zeiss optics and 32GB storage further expandable up to 2TB.
Microsoft is hosting a Windows 10 in New York on October 6 and its likely to showcase these devices at the event. The rumours have also hinted at Windows Hello support for both the phones and support for a dock to support Continuum feature that turns any Windows 10 mobile device into a PC.
Like before, Microsoft Lumia 950 and Lumia 950XL are expected to come with Qi based wireless charging and like Google , Microsoft may opt for USB Type-C port in its new devices.
First Published on October 01, 2015 11:00 pm
